        {
          "id": "N_LOOK_TUBE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The tube station is older than the hallway signage and newer than the building\u2019s optimism.\n\nA laminated label reads: RECEIPTS ARE RECORDS. DO NOT DISCARD.\nBelow it, someone has added pen: \u201cUnless it\u2019s not ours.\u201d",
          "next": "N_TUBE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TUBE_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_TUBE_LOOK_PRINT",
              "text": "look: Dot-matrix printout.",
              "next": "N_LOOK_PRINT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_TUBE_USE_TAKE",
              "text": "use: Take the printout.",
              "next": "N_TAKE_PRINTOUT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_TUBE_USE_ACCEPT",
              "text": "use: Accept and log the notice.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act3.mtaNoticeReceived",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": false
                }
              ],
              "next": "N_ACCEPT_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_TUBE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "R_TO_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOOK_PRINT",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The paper is too clean. The perforated edges are intact.\nThe header is centered, as if the sender expects to be filed.",
          "next": "N_NOTICE_READ_MTA"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_NOTICE_READ_MTA",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "MTA_CONTACT",
          "text": "Okay\u2014 (pause)\n\u201cNOTICE \u2014 NON-LOCAL COMPLIANCE CONDITION.\u201d (pause)\n\u201cSUBJECT NODE: SOL\u2011EARTH\u2011LOCAL.\u201d (pause)\n\u201cACTION: HOLD STATE PENDING DOCUMENTATION.\u201d (pause)\n\u201cMANAGING AUTHORITY: METASTABLE TRANSFER AUTHORITY (MTA).\u201d (pause)\n\u201cREFERENCE: MTA_NOTICE_REF.\u201d",
          "next": "N_LOOK_PRINT_TAG"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOOK_PRINT_TAG",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "There\u2019s a barcode block that looks printed by a different decade than the dot-matrix text. It\u2019s crisp enough to feel like an accusation.",
          "next": "N_PRINT_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PRINT_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_PRINT_ASK_STANDING",
              "text": "ask: \u201cStanding?\u201d",
              "next": "N_STANDING_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_PRINT_ASK_SERVICE",
              "text": "ask: \u201cService class?\u201d",
              "next": "N_SERVICE_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_PRINT_SHOW_REF",
              "text": "show: \u201cReference number.\u201d",
              "next": "N_SHOW_REF_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_PRINT_INTERPRET_REF",
              "text": "ask: Identify the reference format (for the log).",
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "skill",
                  "skill": "bureaucracy",
                  "dc": 12
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N_INTERPRET_REF_PASS",
              "onFailNext": "N_INTERPRET_REF_FAIL"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_PRINT_LOOK_BARCODE",
              "text": "look: Check the barcode format.",
              "next": "N_LOOK_BARCODE"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_PRINT_USE_TAKE",
              "text": "use: Take the printout.",
              "next": "N_TAKE_PRINTOUT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_PRINT_USE_ACCEPT",
              "text": "use: Accept and log the notice.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act3.mtaNoticeReceived",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": false
                }
              ],
              "next": "N_ACCEPT_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_PRINT_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "R_TO_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_STANDING_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Standing?",
          "next": "N_STANDING_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_STANDING_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The notice includes a definition in the margin, like it\u2019s tired of being questioned.\n\n\u201cStanding: recognized eligibility to be processed.\u201d\n\u201cProcessed\u201d is underlined once. The underline is perfectly straight, which is its own kind of threat.",
          "next": "R_TO_PRINT_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_SERVICE_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Service class?",
          "next": "N_SERVICE_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_SERVICE_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Another margin block, pre-emptive.\n\n\u201cSERVICE CLASS: UNRESOLVED.\u201d\n\u201cIncorrect service class assignments may affect standing.\u201d\n\nThe sentence is written like an apology that learned to protect itself.",
          "next": "R_TO_PRINT_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_SHOW_REF_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "MTA_NOTICE_REF.",
          "next": "N_SHOW_REF_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_SHOW_REF_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Saying it out loud makes it feel more real and less defensible.\n\nThe reference string has the shape of an external docket: prefix, jurisdiction stub, and a queue-like tail that implies you are not first.",
          "next": "R_TO_PRINT_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_INTERPRET_REF_PASS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "It reads like external docketing: jurisdiction stub, a processing lane code, then a queue-position tail. It\u2019s designed to be cited, not understood.",
          "next": "R_TO_PRINT_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_INTERPRET_REF_FAIL",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You can\u2019t place it with confidence. It\u2019s too clean, too standardized\u2014like it expects your systems to already agree with it.",
          "next": "R_TO_PRINT_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOOK_BARCODE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "High-contrast and machine-friendly. No smearing. No aging.\n\nIt\u2019s formatted like it expects every reader you own to already agree what it means.",
          "next": "R_TO_PRINT_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOOK_RECORDS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The records door has three locks and a posted schedule.\nThe schedule is handwritten, then photocopied until it becomes law.\n\nSomeone has added: \u201cNO TUBE DROPS INSIDE RECORDS.\u201d\nUnder that: \u201cException: Compliance.\u201d",
          "next": "N_RECORDS_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_RECORDS_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_RECORDS_LOOK_PRINT",
              "text": "look: Dot-matrix printout.",
              "next": "N_LOOK_PRINT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_RECORDS_USE_TAKE",
              "text": "use: Take the printout.",
              "next": "N_TAKE_PRINTOUT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_RECORDS_USE_ACCEPT",
              "text": "use: Accept and log the notice.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act3.mtaNoticeReceived",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": false
                }
              ],
              "next": "N_ACCEPT_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_RECORDS_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "R_TO_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOOK_FAX",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A placard above the wall fax lists numbers by jurisdiction, as if geography still solves things.\n\nThere\u2019s a blank line labeled \u201cNON-LOCAL / OTHER.\u201d The blank line has been used often enough to be glossy.",
          "next": "N_FAX_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_FAX_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_FAX_LOOK_PRINT",
              "text": "look: Dot-matrix printout.",
              "next": "N_LOOK_PRINT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_FAX_ASK_MTA_FAX",
              "text": "ask: \u201cMTA have a fax?\u201d",
              "next": "N_ASK_MTA_FAX_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_FAX_USE_TAKE",
              "text": "use: Take the printout.",
              "next": "N_TAKE_PRINTOUT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_FAX_USE_ACCEPT",
              "text": "use: Accept and log the notice.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act3.mtaNoticeReceived",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": false
                }
              ],
              "next": "N_ACCEPT_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_FAX_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "R_TO_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ASK_MTA_FAX_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "MTA have a fax?",
          "next": "N_ASK_MTA_FAX_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ASK_MTA_FAX_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The placard doesn\u2019t answer. It offers a procedure instead.\n\n\u201cIf destination is unlisted: transmit to ADMIN SERVICES. NOTE \u2018NON-LOCAL\u2019 IN COVER SHEET.\u201d\n\nThe instruction feels like it was written after someone tried to be clever.",
          "next": "R_TO_FAX_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOOK_FIRE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The fire panel has a taped note in block letters: \u201cDO NOT SILENCE WITHOUT INCIDENT NUMBER.\u201d\nBeneath it, in smaller writing: \u201cEven if it\u2019s annoying.\u201d\n\nThe building\u2019s priorities are clear.",
          "next": "N_FIRE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_FIRE_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_FIRE_LOOK_PRINT",
              "text": "look: Dot-matrix printout.",
              "next": "N_LOOK_PRINT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_FIRE_USE_TAKE",
              "text": "use: Take the printout.",
              "next": "N_TAKE_PRINTOUT"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_FIRE_USE_ACCEPT",
              "text": "use: Accept and log the notice.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act3.mtaNoticeReceived",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": false
                }
              ],
              "next": "N_ACCEPT_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_FIRE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "R_TO_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ASK_WHO_SENT_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Who sent this?",
          "next": "N_ASK_WHO_SENT_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ASK_WHO_SENT_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The printout answers the way authorities do\u2014by naming a category instead of a person.\n\n\u201cMANAGING AUTHORITY: METASTABLE TRANSFER AUTHORITY (MTA).\u201d\n\nNo signature. No phone tree. Just an acronym that expects compliance to be its own point of contact.",
          "next": "R_TO_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TAKE_PRINTOUT",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You lift the page from the tray. The paper resists, then releases, like it wants to be on record.\n\nThe tube station light stays lit. It doesn\u2019t thank you. It just waits for the next step you didn\u2019t agree to.",
          "next": "N_TAKE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_TAKE_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_TAKE_ACCEPT",
              "text": "use: Accept and log the notice.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act3.mtaNoticeReceived",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": false
                }
              ],
              "next": "N_ACCEPT_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_TAKE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back to the hallway.",
              "next": "R_TO_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACCEPT_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You treat it as evidence, not mail.\nYou keep the original. You note the header. You keep the barcodes intact.\nYou do not summarize from memory.",
          "next": "N_ACCEPT_POST_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACCEPT_POST_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_ACCEPT_INITIAL_OLEA",
              "text": "use: Add OLEA signatory initials in the margin.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "player.oleaAuthorizedSignatory",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "next": "N_ACCEPT_INITIAL_OLEA_LINE"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ACCEPT_INITIAL_CHECK",
              "text": "use: Add chain-of-custody initials anyway (boring, defensible).",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "player.oleaAuthorizedSignatory",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": false
                }
              ],
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "skill",
                  "skill": "bureaucracy",
                  "dc": 10
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N_ACCEPT_INITIAL_PASS",
              "onFailNext": "N_ACCEPT_INITIAL_FAIL"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ACCEPT_NO_INITIAL",
              "text": "use: No annotation. Keep it clean.",
              "next": "N_ACCEPT_NO_INITIAL_LINE"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACCEPT_INITIAL_OLEA_LINE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You add OLEA signatory initials in the margin, small and boring.\nA chain of custody is mostly handwriting that refuses to be interesting.",
          "next": "N_ACCEPT_RESOLVE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACCEPT_INITIAL_PASS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You add initials and a timestamp in the margin\u2014nothing authoritative, just consistent.\nIt reads like a person who expects to be questioned and intends to survive it.",
          "next": "N_ACCEPT_RESOLVE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACCEPT_INITIAL_FAIL",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You start to write, then stop.\nWithout standing to claim, handwriting is just another thing that can be argued about later.",
          "next": "N_ACCEPT_RESOLVE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACCEPT_NO_INITIAL_LINE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You don\u2019t initial it. You still handle it like it will be read aloud later, by someone paid to misunderstand you.",
          "next": "N_ACCEPT_RESOLVE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_ACCEPT_RESOLVE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The reference number\u2014MTA_NOTICE_REF\u2014becomes something you can cite without sounding like you made it up.\n\nThe tube station indicator finally clicks off. Not resolved. Just recorded.",
          "next": "END_RECEIVE_MTA_NOTICE"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_RECEIVE_MTA_NOTICE",
          "type": "end",
          "outcomeId": "receive_mta_notice",
          "effects": [
            {
              "key": "act3.mtaNoticeReceived",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "key": "inventory.items",
              "action": "add",
              "value": "ITEM_MTA_NOTICE"
            },
            {
              "key": "act3.mtaNoticeRef",
              "action": "set",
              "value": "MTA_NOTICE_REF"
            },
            {
              "key": "objectives.buildEvidencePacket",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "key": "objectives.fileTemporaryVariance",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LEAVE_DOWN_LINE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You head down toward the Admin Lobby and Kiosk.\nThe hallway swallows the tube station\u2019s patience without argument.",
          "next": "END_LEAVE_DOWN"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_LEAVE_DOWN",
          "type": "end"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LEAVE_RIGHT_LINE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You turn toward the Copy and Fax Room.\nMachines that replicate paper also replicate blame. You go anyway.",
          "next": "END_LEAVE_RIGHT"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_LEAVE_RIGHT",
          "type": "end"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LEAVE_FORWARD_LINE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You move toward the Operations Corridor.\nSomewhere behind you, the tube station stays quiet\u2014like it has done its part and is waiting to see if you do yours.",
          "next": "END_LEAVE_FORWARD"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_LEAVE_FORWARD",
          "type": "end"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LEAVE_LEFT_LINE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You head left toward the SPINDLE observation deck.\nThe notice remains what it is: a hold state dressed up as administrative routine.",
          "next": "END_LEAVE_LEFT"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_LEAVE_LEFT",
          "type": "end"
        },
        {
